codex
The generator design is now fixed: PostgREST/service-role is used only for read-only ledger inspection; it never attempts DDL. Each pending migration is split at top-level SQL statement boundaries, and the emitted SQL Editor bundle executes each statement dynamically inside a per-file ledger guard, then records its SHA-256 checksum atomically. This preserves idempotence even for migrations containing functions or nested `DO $$` blocks.
