# Codex Proof Gate

Use this skill when asked to verify a repo, finish a code/config change, prepare a handoff, or sanity-check Codex/operator tooling.

## Workflow

1. Run `/Users/liamcann/.codex-meta/bin/codex-proof-gate <target-path>`.
2. Use `--quick` only when the target is large or the user explicitly asks for a fast pass.
3. Treat failures as blockers unless the user asked for a diagnostic-only pass.
4. Report the evidence file path and the highest-signal failed checks.

## Rules

- Do not print secret values. The proof gate reports counts and redacted command output.
- Prefer targeted project checks when a repo has its own documented verification command.
- For frontend work, pair this with the Playwright skill and screenshots.
- For Codex meta-work, also run `/Users/liamcann/.codex-meta/bin/codex-rack secrets scan`.

